      • legacyStyleQuoting

        public boolean legacyStyleQuoting()
        Adds a default implementation returning DEFAULT_LEGACY_STYLE_QUOTING, this to not requiring any change to other classes using this interface.
        Returns:
        whether or not the parsing will interpret \" (see quotationCharacter()) as an inner quote. Reason why this is configurable is that this interpretation conflicts with "standard" RFC for CSV parsing, see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4180. This also makes it impossible to enter some combinations of characters, e.g. """abc\""", when expecting "abc\".
